name: Fried rice
description: Fried rice is a dish of cooked rice that has been stir-fried in a wok or a frying pan and is usually mixed with other ingredients such as eggs, vegetables, seafood, or meat. It is often eaten by itself or as an accompaniment to another dish

name: Iced Orange
description: It's basically orange juice, water, and sugar, and is refreshingly sweet and citrusy.

name: Iced Tea
description: Iced tea is a form of cold tea.

name: Nila goreng
description: Nila goreng is a hot dish consisting of deep fried tilapia fish . Ikan goreng literally means fried fish in Indonesian and Malay languages.

name: Ayam penyet
description: Ayam penyet Javanese for squeezed fried chicken is Indonesian more precisely East Javanese cuisine fried chicken dish consisting of fried chicken that is squeezed with the pestle against the mortar to make it softer, and is served with sambal, slices of cucumbers, fried tofu, and tempeh mostly cucumber.

name: Kebuli rice
description: an Indonesian variation of pilaf. It consists of rice cooked in goat meat broth, goat milk, and clarified butter or most often ghee. It is popular among the Arab community in Indonesia and Betawi people in Jakarta.

name: Lamb satay
description: Originated from Java, Sate or Satay kambing is a popular Indonesian street food dish of seasoned, skewered and then grilled or barbecued sliced Lamb, served with a sauce made of peanut combined with sweet soy

name: Rendang
description: Slow-cooked spicy meat dish originating from the Minangkabau region, usually made with beef simmered with coconut milk and a mixture of spices

name: Chicken satay
description: Originated from Java, Sate or Satay Ayam is a popular Indonesian street food dish of seasoned, skewered and then grilled or barbecued sliced chicken, served with a sauce made of peanut combined with sweet soy

name: Gado-gado
description: Indonesian salad of boiled vegetables, eggs, tempeh, and tofu, served with peanut sauce dressing

name: Soto ayam
description: Soto ayam is a traditional Indonesian dish with ingredients such as chicken, lontong, noodles, and rice vermicelli. Soto ayam is popular in Singapore, Malaysia and Suriname.

name: Bakso
description: Indonesian meatball soup with broth, noodles, tofu, vegetables, and various toppings

name: Nasi Uduk
description: Steamed rice cooked with coconut milk and served with various side dishes

name: Mie Goreng
description: Indonesian stir-fried noodles with vegetables, chicken or seafood, and sweet soy sauce

name: Sambal Udang
description: Spicy shrimp dish cooked in chili-based sauce, often served with rice

name: Ayam Bakar
description: Indonesian grilled chicken marinated in various spices and sweet soy sauce

name: Nasi Kuning
description: Yellow rice cooked with coconut milk and turmeric, served with various side dishes

name: Sop Buntut
description: Indonesian oxtail soup with carrots, potatoes, and various spices

name: Lontong Sayur
description: Rice cake served with vegetable curry and various toppings

name: Lele goreng
description: Pecel lele or pecak lele is an Indonesian deep-fried Clarias catfish dish originating from Lamongan, East Java, Indonesia.

name: Siomay
description: Indonesian-style steamed fish dumplings served with peanut sauce

name: Nasi Campur
description: Mixed rice dish with various small portions of meat, vegetables, peanuts, eggs, and fried-shrimp krupuk

name: Bebek Goreng
description: Indonesian-style deep-fried duck often served with rice and sambal

name: Ikan Bakar
description: Grilled fish marinated in various spices, often served with rice and sambal

name: Sayur Asem
description: Sour vegetable soup with tamarind, often containing peanuts, corn, and jackfruit

name: Martabak Manis
description: Sweet thick pancake filled with various toppings like chocolate, cheese, and peanuts

name: Soto betawi
description: Soto Betawi made of beef or beef offal, cooked in a cow milk or coconut milk broth, with fried potato and tomato.

name: Pisang Goreng
description: Deep-fried banana fritters, often served as a snack or dessert

name: Rawon
description: East Javanese black beef soup with kluwek nut that gives it a dark color

name: Opor Ayam
description: Chicken cooked in coconut milk with various spices, traditionally served during Eid al-Fitr

name: Ketoprak
description: Vegetarian dish of tofu, vegetables, rice cake, and rice vermicelli with peanut sauce dressing

name: Pempek
description: Palembang-style fishcake served with sweet and sour sauce

name: Gulai Kambing
description: Indonesian curry made with goat meat or mutton in a spicy coconut milk-based sauce

name: Nasi Liwet
description: Javanese-style rice cooked with coconut milk, chicken broth, and various spices

name: Bubur Ayam
description: Indonesian rice porridge topped with shredded chicken, green onions, and crispy fried shallots

name: Kerak Telor
description: Betawi egg and rice crust dish often sold as street food in Jakarta

name: Sate Lilit
description: Balinese minced fish satay mixed with coconut and spices, wrapped around lemongrass or bamboo sticks

name: Cendol
description: Iced sweet dessert with green rice flour jelly, coconut milk, and palm sugar syrup

name: Mie Aceh
description: Spicy noodle dish from Aceh, typically served with beef or seafood

name: Gudeg
description: Javanese dish made from young jackfruit cooked with coconut milk and various spices

name: Balado Terong
description: Spicy eggplant dish cooked with chili paste, often served as a side dish

name: Beef Kebab
description: kebab, dish of Middle Eastern or Central Asian origin that typically combines small pieces of meat such as lamb or beef with vegetables on a skewer and is then grilled

name: Chicken Kebab
description: kebab, dish of Middle Eastern or Central Asian origin that typically combines small pieces of meat such as chicken  with vegetables on a skewer and is then grilled

name: Chicken biryani
description: Biryani is a celebratory rice and meat dish cherished in the Indian sub-continent. A traditional biryani consists of fluffy basmati rice layered over tender & succulent pieces of chicken, accompanied with the mesmerizing aromas of spices, herbs & caramelized onion

name: Soto Banjar
description: South Kalimantan-style chicken soup with rice cakes, potato patties, and hard-boiled eggs

name: Es Teler
description: Indonesian cold and sweet dessert with avocado, young coconut meat, jackfruit, and condensed milk

name: Sambal Matah
description: Balinese raw shallot and lemongrass relish, often served as a condiment
